<subSubSection id="44FFB0EAFFA1FFBD158BF9DBB29AF934" pageId="10" pageNumber="235" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="0C5AE361FFA1FFBD158BF9DBB29AF934" blockId="10.[151,1437,726,1761]" pageId="10" pageNumber="235">
<emphasis id="3E913F73FFA1FFBD158BF9DBB703F9A0" bold="true" box="[199,308,1626,1652]" pageId="10" pageNumber="235">Remarks</emphasis>
. This species has similar male genitalia to 
<taxonomicName id="CBE598E2FFA1FFBD1658F9DAB54EF9A0" box="[788,889,1626,1652]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Drabescus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="235" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kempi">
<emphasis id="3E913F73FFA1FFBD1658F9DAB54EF9A0" box="[788,889,1626,1652]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="235">D. kempi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but has strongly divergent basal processes of the aedeagal shaft compared to those in 
<emphasis id="3E913F73FFA1FFBD1779F9FEB494F94C" box="[565,675,1662,1688]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="235">
<taxonomicName id="CBE598E2FFA1FFBD1779F9FEB4A9F94C" box="[565,670,1662,1688]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Drabescus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="235" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kempi">D. kempi</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
The two species also differ in coloration, the former being entirely black with a few small orange yellow markings compared to reddish orange coloration with anterior marginal ivory stripe on the fore margin of the head and the lateral margins of pronotum in the latter species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
